The paper deals with algorithms for computing graph distances and involves techniques from computational geometry, data structures, and combinatorics. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves combinatorial analysis of algorithms, which suggests cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) as possible sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with parameterized complexity, which suggests cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as a possible sub-category.
